The paper discusses the dynamics of deep neural networks and their training using gradient descent. This topic is primarily related to machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper involves the study of ordinary differential equations, which falls under information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the performance of deep neural networks in image classification tasks, which is related to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper involves the study of the generalization features of deep neural networks, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
